        {
            "id": "e671ba7ef28f41dc926b1",
            "questionText": "An archaeological team unearths an ancient textile sample weighing $!$100$!$ grams from a tomb. To determine its age, a radiocarbon analysis is performed. The half-life of Carbon-14 is $!$5730$!$ years. A living organism's carbon exhibits an initial activity of $!$226$!$ Bq per $!$100$!$ grams of carbon. The textile sample displays a measured activity of $!$28$!$ Bq, which includes a background radiation level of $!$4$!$ Bq. Calculate the age of the textile in years.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "db8dab33135245f4bc657",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by finding the net activity due to Carbon-14 decay. Subtract the background radiation from the measured activity.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "24"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "Bq",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "04218446cd96447b8ffdf",
                    "stepText": "Great, now compute the ratio of the net activity to the initial activity of living carbon. This ratio is unitless. What is the value of $!$A/A_0$!$?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.1062"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "7f8a2a905ae94d2f87572",
                    "stepText": "Now, to use the radiocarbon decay law, we need to identify the correct formula that represents exponential decay based on half-life. Please choose the correct decay formula.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "4ba46951-f583-43e5-8ee2-7582647271d3"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A = A_0 \\times (1/2)^{(t/T_{1/2})}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A = A_0 \\times e^{-t/T_{1/2}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$A = A_0 - t \\times (1/2)^{T_{1/2}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "4e0e955f69b04c45abf09",
                    "stepText": "Continuing, we need the rearranged version of the decay formula to solve for the time $!$t$!$. Identify the correct rearranged formula from the following options.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "4ba46951-f583-43e5-8ee2-7582647271d3",
                        "b9ca20c3-e249-4bc5-8d94-4d2bceee779d"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$t = T_{1/2} \\times \\frac{\\ln(A/A_0)}{\\ln(1/2)}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$t = T_{1/2} \\times \\ln(A/A_0)$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$t = \\ln((1/2)^{A/A_0}) \\times T_{1/2}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "96d369c9bd2e4a7c9be4e",
                    "stepText": "Next, calculate the ratio of logarithms, that is $!$\\frac{\\ln(A/A_0)}{\\ln(1/2)}$!$, using your earlier computed ratio $!$A/A_0 \\approx 0.1062$!$. What value is obtained (approximately)?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "3.234"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "338b5271b8dc4c0ba732f",
                    "stepText": "Finally, use the rearranged decay formula with the half-life and the logarithmic ratio you computed to determine the age of the textile. Multiply the half-life ($!$5730$!$ years) by your logarithmic ratio. What is the approximate age of the textile in years?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "18520"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "years",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "b9ca20c3-e249-4bc5-8d94-4d2bceee779d",
                        "4ba46951-f583-43e5-8ee2-7582647271d3"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
