            "questionText": "A typical residential smoke alarm contains $!$0.9$!$ microcuries of Americium-241. Given that $!$1$!$ curie is defined as $!$3.7 \\times 10^{10}$!$ disintegrations per second, calculate the number of alpha particles emitted per second by the Americium-241 in the smoke alarm. (Give your answer in disintegrations per second, rounding to the nearest whole number.)",
